1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper primarily focuses on using deep convolutional neural networks to analyze visual characteristics of real estate photos, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper also involves developing a framework for automated value assessment, which involves using machine learning algorithms to estimate the market value of houses. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper involves developing a novel framework for automated value assessment using a combination of home characteristics and visual features, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper involves analyzing a large dataset of real estate photos and metadata to develop a method for estimating the luxury level of real estate photos, which falls under the domain of information retrieval. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper involves analyzing visual characteristics of real estate photos, which falls under the domain of multimedia.
